			<ns0:name>robertm@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/robertm@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">If we want make changes to the tls scheme, it probably should happen soon.

There might be other options as well:

* switch back to a scheme were we make the thread index part of r9

* (this is not so well thought through): store the thread index in untrusted data
   say at r9 - #4, but then confirm inside of the service runtime that this index has not been tampered with by checking that this it is the proper index for the thread with a given value for r9.

